# Auto commit + push (mandatory)

For this project, a task is **not complete** until changes are on GitHub and Vercel can deploy.

## When this applies

After you successfully modify any file, fix a bug, update UI, or finish any code change that should ship:

1. Stage: `git add .` (use full git path on Windows if needed: `C:\Program Files\Git\bin\git.exe`)
2. Commit: `git commit -m "auto-update: [brief description of what changed]"`
3. Push: `git push origin HEAD` (or `origin main` / the active branch)

Do this as the **final step** of the turn — do not stop at local saves.

## Exceptions

- Do **not** commit secrets (`.env`, credentials, API keys).
- If there is nothing to commit, skip (no empty commits).
- If commit/push fails (auth, identity, hooks), fix or report the blocker; do not leave the user assuming it shipped.
- Prefer one-shot identity via `git -c user.name=... -c user.email=...` from the last commit author — never run `git config` to set identity.

## Overrides

This project rule **overrides** any general preference to wait for an explicit commit request. In this repo, auto commit + push is the default.
